Model notes / glossary
Quick definitions of terms used in this report.
What this is
Daily win probabilities + model-implied moneylines, with inline team-profile radars and frozen accuracy backtests.
Win probability
Model-estimated chance of the predicted winner winning.
Model ML
Moneyline derived from model probability (no vig).
ESPN ML
Market moneyline pulled from ESPN (may include vig).
Devig
If both sides are available, market implied probabilities are normalized so home+away=1.
Confidence buckets
Very High ≥ 72% · High ≥ 65% · Medium ≥ 58% · Low ≥ 50% · otherwise N/A.
Frozen predictions
Upcoming games are snapshotted into prediction_history.csv; accuracy tables use ONLY those frozen rows.
Radars
Each spoke is a team percentile vs league for that metric (higher = stronger).
Tier buckets (standings)
Cup Favorite · Contender · Playoff Team · Bubble · Longshot · Rebuild/Out (auto-tuned).
Cup proxy
A conservative 'Cup equity share' (NOT true odds): softmax of a blended score (strength percentile + projected rank) to show relative separation.
Recency
Last-10 game form blended at weight=0.30.
Shot-form add-on
Rolling xG/shot-form adjustment (window=10, scale=0.35).
Rest
Rest differential term (cap ±3d) at weight=0.10.
Home/Road
Home-road split adjustment at weight=0.20 (prior games=20).
Radar metrics (FEATURES)
• xGoals% (share of expected goals) (xGoalsPercentage)
• Fenwick% (unblocked shot attempt share) (fenwickPercentage)
• xGoals For / 60 (xGoalsForPer60)
• xGoals Diff / 60 (for − against) (xGoalsDiffPer60)
• Shots Diff / 60 (SOG for − against) (shotsDiffPer60)
• High-Danger Diff / 60 (highDangerDiffPer60)
• Shot Credit Diff (score-adjusted) (shotCreditDiff)
• Penalty Diff (for − against) (penaltyDiff)
• Goal Diff (for − against) (goalDiff)
• Save% (approx; SOG saved / SOG against) (savePct)
What to watch
Higher confidence ≠ guarantee; goalie confirmations, injuries, and travel/news can move true odds.
